This way of doing software, this way of doing computation, is a reinvention=
 from the ground up, and it=E2=80=99s not easy. Accelerated computing is a =
full-stack problem. It=E2=80=99s not as easy as general purpose computing. =
The CPU is a miracle: high level programming languages, great compilers, al=
most anybody can write reasonably good programs, because the CPU is so flex=
ible. However, its ability to scale in performance has ended and we need a =
new approach. Accelerated computing is full stack. You have to re-engineer =
everything from the top-down and bottom-up, from the chip to systems to the=
