ns.

This is correct, and bears on the points below. The vast majority of comput=
ing to date is still single-threaded: data centers are huge, with a ton of =
CPUs, but each individual job is by-and-large run on a single thread on a s=
ingle CPU that can handle an array of tasks. Accelerated computing, on the =
other hand, is highly parallel: you run one job across multiple GPUs that a=
re much simpler in their execution pipeline; this, by extension, means abst=
racting complexity up into the software.

*Accelerated Computing is a Data-Center Scale Problem*

( https://videopress.com/embed/BObsR7uQ?hd=3D1&cover=3D1&loop=3D0&autoPlay=
=3D0&permalink=3D1&muted=3D0&controls=3D1&playsinline=3D0&useAverageColor=
