The second is that it=E2=80=99s a data-center scale problem. The reason why=
 it=E2=80=99s a data-center scale problem is today the data-center is the c=
omputer. Unlike the past when the PC was a computer or your phone was a com=
puter, today your data center is the computer. Your application runs across=
 the entire data center. And therefore, it=E2=80=99s vital that you have to=
 understand how to optimize chips, the compute, the software, across a NIC,=
 the switch, all the way to other end in a distributed computing way.

This is the hardware manifestation of the previous point: if you are execut=
ing across multiple GPUs then your target is not any one core or any one ch=
ip, but rather the entire system that contains multiple chips.

*Accelerated Computing is Multi-Domain*

( https://videopress.com/embed/YY3Lf8pf?hd=3D1&cover=3D1&loop=3D0&autoPlay=
=3D0&permalink=3D1&muted=3D0&controls=3D1&playsinline=3D0&useAverageColor=
